1
00:01:00,869 --> 00:01:02,469
Subtitles by Johnny Depp

2
00:01:02,870 --> 00:01:06,863
Hello, Mr. Michaux!
You're no bother at all!

3
00:01:07,842 --> 00:01:11,045
I'm at the park,
practicing my boomerang.

4
00:01:11,045 --> 00:01:15,038
I do it before the office,
to relieve stress.

5
00:01:15,350 --> 00:01:19,343
Dinner, Wednesday evening?
I'd be delighted!

6
00:01:22,523 --> 00:01:24,525
Hi!

7
00:01:24,525 --> 00:01:27,695
- Coming to the game Wednesday?
- No, I have a dinner party.

8
00:01:27,695 --> 00:01:30,064
- Charlie. Coffee, please.
- What dinner party?

9
00:01:30,064 --> 00:01:33,268
- One of our customers invited me.
- Why you?

10
00:01:33,268 --> 00:01:37,261
At the bank, he stops
at my window and chats.

11
00:01:37,305 --> 00:01:39,841
- What about?
- Everything... politics,

12
00:01:39,841 --> 00:01:41,442
entertainment, sports...

13
00:01:41,442 --> 00:01:43,511
He asks for my opinion
and I tell him.

14
00:01:43,511 --> 00:01:46,948
Why would he ask
an idiot like you?

15
00:01:46,948 --> 00:01:50,518
Listen, there'll be
big shots at that dinner!

16
00:01:50,518 --> 00:01:53,855
Mr. Perier says they're very
interested in my ideas.

17
00:01:53,855 --> 00:01:56,924
So maybe the idiot
isn't me, okay?

18
00:01:56,924 --> 00:01:58,559
That's wonderful!

19
00:01:58,559 --> 00:02:01,095
I'll definitely be there
on Wednesday,

20
00:02:01,095 --> 00:02:05,088
unless something
unexpected...

21
00:02:13,441 --> 00:02:15,443
- You coming or going?
- Going.

22
00:02:15,443 --> 00:02:17,378
To Biarritz.

23
00:02:17,378 --> 00:02:19,847
- What's in Biarritz?
- It's my dad's birthday.

24
00:02:19,847 --> 00:02:21,349
Say hello for me.

25
00:02:21,349 --> 00:02:23,351
A coffee, please.

26
00:02:23,351 --> 00:02:26,587
- You're coming Wednesday?
- No, I'm busy. Are you going?

27
00:02:26,587 --> 00:02:30,580
Sure. I'm in a bind.
I don't have an idiot.

28
00:02:30,892 --> 00:02:34,362
I've looked all over.
Got one on hand?

29
00:02:34,362 --> 00:02:38,355
No, but I'll think about it.
I'm late.

30
00:02:41,903 --> 00:02:43,671
What's that?

31
00:02:43,671 --> 00:02:46,074
Dad collects them.
A beauty, huh?

32
00:02:46,074 --> 00:02:48,476
18th century.
He'll love it.

33
00:02:48,476 --> 00:02:51,612
- Your dad collects ladles?
- He has over 300 of them.

34
00:02:51,612 --> 00:02:53,548
He's retired.
Keeps him busy.

35
00:02:53,548 --> 00:02:57,518
Interesting! Could he discuss
his passion in public,

36
00:02:57,518 --> 00:03:00,621
- tell us the story of ladles?
- No, Pierre.

37
00:03:00,621 --> 00:03:03,524
- Does he come to Paris?
- No, Pierre, not Dad.

38
00:03:03,524 --> 00:03:05,893
What? It's a very
original hobby.

39
00:03:05,893 --> 00:03:09,530
- You want him for your dinner?
- How can you say that?

40
00:03:09,530 --> 00:03:12,433
I'd take your dad
to an idiot dinner?

41
00:03:12,433 --> 00:03:14,001
Yes.

42
00:03:14,001 --> 00:03:16,037
You think
I'm a bastard, eh?

43
00:03:16,037 --> 00:03:17,071
Yes.

44
00:03:17,071 --> 00:03:19,574
I was just kidding.

45
00:03:19,574 --> 00:03:23,567
But I don't have an idiot yet.
I'm panicked.

46
00:03:39,026 --> 00:03:43,019
Hi, there.

47
00:03:44,499 --> 00:03:47,101
Sorry!

48
00:03:47,101 --> 00:03:51,094
Thanks.

49
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:03,473
- Sorry, it fell out of my folder.
- That's okay.

50
00:04:05,787 --> 00:04:08,423
- Don't you recognize it?
- What?

51
00:04:08,423 --> 00:04:12,416
The Eiffel Tower! Made of matches.
346,422 to be exact.

52
00:04:14,929 --> 00:04:16,597
You did that?

53
00:04:16,597 --> 00:04:18,132
One of my finest pieces.

54
00:04:18,132 --> 00:04:22,125
- You've done others?
- Are you kidding?

55
00:04:25,873 --> 00:04:28,142
Take the problem of lift.

56
00:04:28,142 --> 00:04:32,135
In this construction,
that was the biggest challenge.

57
00:04:33,915 --> 00:04:35,950
But let's start
from the beginning.

58
00:04:35,950 --> 00:04:39,943
What is
a suspension bridge?

59
00:04:40,855 --> 00:04:44,848
The angle of the matches can't be
a tenth of a degree off!

60
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:49,753
A tenth of a degree,
think of it!

61
00:04:53,534 --> 00:04:57,527
The Concorde was
a different problem.

62
00:05:04,812 --> 00:05:07,815
- Here's a little quiz.
- We've arrived!

63
00:05:07,815 --> 00:05:10,818
Which took me longer,
Eiffel or Concorde?

64
00:05:10,818 --> 00:05:13,921
- We've arrived!
- Really?

65
00:05:13,921 --> 00:05:17,914
Already?
Time did fly!

66
00:05:24,832 --> 00:05:28,825
Pierre Brochant, please.
This is Jean Cordier.

67
00:05:29,937 --> 00:05:31,672
Pierre? I've got one!

68
00:05:31,672 --> 00:05:35,665
- What's he like?
- A world champion!

69
00:07:48,909 --> 00:07:50,645
How's the soccer fan?

70
00:07:50,645 --> 00:07:53,981
"Marseilles are turds!
Marseilles are turds!"

71
00:07:53,981 --> 00:07:57,718
Auxerre will get it
Wednesday!

72
00:07:57,718 --> 00:07:59,754
Look at that asshole!

73
00:07:59,754 --> 00:08:03,747
- Sorry, Louisette.
- I'm used to it.

74
00:08:05,926 --> 00:08:08,929
Brochant Publishers here.
Mr. Pignon, please.

75
00:08:08,929 --> 00:08:10,431
Speaking.

76
00:08:10,431 --> 00:08:12,933
Mr. Brochant for you.

77
00:08:12,933 --> 00:08:14,402
- Mr. Pignon?
- Yes.

78
00:08:14,402 --> 00:08:17,204
My friend Jean Cordier
gave me your number.

79
00:08:17,204 --> 00:08:21,208
- You met him on the train.
- Yes, of course.

80
00:08:21,208 --> 00:08:24,178
He said a lot about you.
I want to meet you.

81
00:08:24,178 --> 00:08:26,714
To meet me?

82
00:08:26,714 --> 00:08:29,817
Franois Pignon!
He was so awed,

83
00:08:29,817 --> 00:08:33,810
he was speechless.
It'll be a delight!

84
00:08:36,724 --> 00:08:39,493
- Who's Michaux bringing?
- A boomerang collector.

85
00:08:39,493 --> 00:08:42,096
- That's a good one.
- Priceless, I hear.

86
00:08:42,096 --> 00:08:44,965
- How many of us will there be?
- 10, with Pignon.

87
00:08:44,965 --> 00:08:48,958
It's shaping up.

88
00:08:52,306 --> 00:08:56,299
- Shit!
- What is it?

89
00:09:00,147 --> 00:09:04,140
Christine!

90
00:09:25,806 --> 00:09:29,477
- Did you cancel your dinner?
- My God, that's cold!

91
00:09:29,477 --> 00:09:32,813
- So, did you cancel?
- A sore back needs heat.

92
00:09:32,813 --> 00:09:35,316
- Dr. Sorbier said ice.
- You reached him?

93
00:09:35,316 --> 00:09:37,818
In his car.
He'll be here soon.

94
00:09:37,818 --> 00:09:41,811
Great. I need a drink.
A splash of scotch.

95
00:09:43,023 --> 00:09:47,027
- Did your sore back make you deaf?
- No, I didn't cancel.

96
00:09:47,027 --> 00:09:49,530
You're still going
to that sinister dinner?

97
00:09:49,530 --> 00:09:53,523
It's great fun.
You think it's sinister...

98
00:09:53,801 --> 00:09:57,138
Don't sulk just
because I enjoy it!

99
00:09:57,138 --> 00:10:01,131
Come on. Stay with me.
You know I'm not feeling well.

100
00:10:01,475 --> 00:10:05,179
So come with me, for a change.
You'll have a blast.

101
00:10:05,179 --> 00:10:08,015
Making fun
of some poor guy?

102
00:10:08,015 --> 00:10:12,008
But he's an idiot!
Idiots are fair game.

103
00:10:12,052 --> 00:10:14,855
A drink at his place,
then dinner.

104
00:10:14,855 --> 00:10:16,957
- At a restaurant?
- No,

105
00:10:16,957 --> 00:10:18,826
his friend has organized
a big dinner.

106
00:10:18,826 --> 00:10:22,363
I'm nervous.
Which one?

107
00:10:22,363 --> 00:10:25,566
- They're the same.
- This one's redder.

108
00:10:25,566 --> 00:10:29,559
It's more festive.

109
00:10:29,937 --> 00:10:33,930
Mustn't forget
my model file.

110
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:38,078
He wants to do a book!
On my models, you realize?

111
00:10:38,078 --> 00:10:40,281
Hurry, you'll be late.

112
00:10:40,281 --> 00:10:42,016
You asked him here?

113
00:10:42,016 --> 00:10:45,920
To study him before dinner.
I hear he's fabulous.

114
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:49,423
I'll leave you two together.
Enjoy!

115
00:10:49,423 --> 00:10:51,959
- Where are you going?
- I have a dinner too.

116
00:10:51,959 --> 00:10:55,196
- I didn't want to go, but...
- Dinner with whom?

117
00:10:55,196 --> 00:10:58,199
Is it him?
I don't want to meet him.

118
00:10:58,199 --> 00:11:02,203
No, it's the doctor.

119
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:06,196
- Dr. Sorbier.
- Come on up, Doctor.

120
00:11:08,075 --> 00:11:10,945
Good evening, Doctor.

121
00:11:10,945 --> 00:11:13,480
Fix him. He has an important
dinner tonight.

122
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:15,883
- Christine!
- An idiot dinner.

123
00:11:15,883 --> 00:11:18,886
Each regular has
to bring an idiot.

124
00:11:18,886 --> 00:11:20,321
Christine, please!

125
00:11:20,321 --> 00:11:22,890
The idiots don't know
why they've been picked.

126
00:11:22,890 --> 00:11:25,860
The fun is making them talk.
Hilarious!

127
00:11:25,860 --> 00:11:29,853
Not to me, so I'm leaving.
Good night, doctor.

128
00:11:34,068 --> 00:11:38,072
Sorry. I called you
to fix my back, not my marriage.

129
00:11:38,072 --> 00:11:42,065
- Can I wash my hands?
- First door on the left.

130
00:11:42,343 --> 00:11:46,336
In college, we used
to invite ugly girls.

131
00:11:46,447 --> 00:11:48,582
The ugliest one
got a prize.

132
00:11:48,582 --> 00:11:50,584
Yes, we did that too.

133
00:11:50,584 --> 00:11:53,621
- But idiots are funnier.
- But less definite.

134
00:11:53,621 --> 00:11:56,290
Some idiots are quite obvious.

135
00:11:56,290 --> 00:12:00,283
Mine's unmistakable.

136
00:12:03,530 --> 00:12:05,599
You look great.

137
00:12:05,599 --> 00:12:07,268
Thanks, Louisette.

138
00:12:07,268 --> 00:12:11,261
Have a nice evening.
Dazzle them!

139
00:12:12,072 --> 00:12:13,941
- A friend of yours?
- No.

140
00:12:13,941 --> 00:12:15,943
My friends are not
that dumb.

141
00:12:15,943 --> 00:12:19,936
We pick aces.
This is big league.

142
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:22,549
- Where do you find them?
- It's hard.

143
00:12:22,549 --> 00:12:26,020
A real manhunt.
We have scouts who tip us off.

144
00:12:26,020 --> 00:12:30,013
Fifth lumbar vertebra!

145
00:12:36,096 --> 00:12:38,999
- Is it serious?
- No, but call off your dinner.

146
00:12:38,999 --> 00:12:41,602
- No!
- Rest your back tonight.

147
00:12:41,602 --> 00:12:43,938
- I'll stop by tomorrow.
- But, doctor...

148
00:12:43,938 --> 00:12:45,639
I have a prime idiot coming!

149
00:12:45,639 --> 00:12:49,109
Give me a shot!
I don't care! Anything!

150
00:12:49,109 --> 00:12:53,102
Ice-bag and rest, or you'll be
out for three weeks.

151
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:55,316
I'm jinxed.

152
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:57,584
My phone book, please.

153
00:12:57,584 --> 00:13:01,577
The phone.

154
00:13:01,956 --> 00:13:05,949
What's his name again?
Franois Pignon.

155
00:13:10,230 --> 00:13:12,299
- What does he do?
- He's a tax man.

156
00:13:12,299 --> 00:13:14,768
Isn't that dangerous?
What if he finds out?

157
00:13:14,768 --> 00:13:18,761
He won't. We're careful.
No idiot ever found out.

158
00:13:21,008 --> 00:13:23,110
He's out.

159
00:13:23,110 --> 00:13:26,146
- Holy shit!
- What?

160
00:13:26,146 --> 00:13:30,139
His message. He tries
to be witty. It's pathetic.

161
00:13:31,752 --> 00:13:35,255
Franois is out,
but don't pout!

162
00:13:35,255 --> 00:13:39,248
No need to weep,
wait for the beep!

163
00:13:40,327 --> 00:13:42,663
Your turn to peep!

164
00:13:42,663 --> 00:13:46,656
- Isn't he something?
- Outstanding, I'd say.

165
00:13:47,401 --> 00:13:51,394
- Here he is.
- Don't move, I'll get it.

166
00:13:53,007 --> 00:13:54,775
It's Franois Pignon.

167
00:13:54,775 --> 00:13:58,779
6th floor,
on the left.

168
00:13:58,779 --> 00:14:00,481
He's coming.

169
00:14:00,481 --> 00:14:03,684
I'll leave you a sedative.
Take two if you're in pain.

170
00:14:03,684 --> 00:14:07,488
- Wait for him. It'll be fun.
- No. I'm late.

171
00:14:07,488 --> 00:14:10,124
See you tomorrow. Call me at home
if it gets worse.

172
00:14:10,124 --> 00:14:14,128
See you.
Leave the door open.

173
00:14:14,128 --> 00:14:16,663
- Do me a favor.
- Certainly.

174
00:14:16,663 --> 00:14:20,656
Never invite me to dinner.
I'd wonder!

175
00:14:28,509 --> 00:14:32,502
- Good evening.
- Evening, sir.

176
00:14:32,746 --> 00:14:35,849
Go on in. It's open.

177
00:14:35,849 --> 00:14:39,842
Thanks.

178
00:14:43,524 --> 00:14:46,093
Good evening, Mr. Pignon!
Come on in!

179
00:14:46,093 --> 00:14:48,695
I can't get up.

180
00:14:48,695 --> 00:14:52,199
I twisted my back.
We'll have to put off our dinner.

181
00:14:52,199 --> 00:14:55,536
I'm sorry for you.
A sore back is no fun.

182
00:14:55,536 --> 00:14:58,105
It's silly. What are you doing
next Wednesday?

183
00:14:58,105 --> 00:15:00,674
Next Wednesday... nothing.

184
00:15:00,674 --> 00:15:04,667
My friend's giving another dinner.
You're invited.

185
00:15:04,845 --> 00:15:07,481
How very nice.

186
00:15:07,481 --> 00:15:11,474
We missed you today.
We won't miss you next week.

187
00:15:12,119 --> 00:15:16,112
...l'm talking about
the authentic boomerang,

188
00:15:16,423 --> 00:15:20,416
not those you find
in Sydney souvenir stores.

189
00:15:21,161 --> 00:15:25,154
The primitive boomerang
of proud aboriginal warriors,

190
00:15:27,167 --> 00:15:28,769
that boomerang

191
00:15:28,769 --> 00:15:32,762
has a dynamism, a motion

192
00:15:33,307 --> 00:15:37,300
when it's thrown correctly,
that is miraculous!

193
00:15:38,212 --> 00:15:39,480
How are you?

194
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:43,217
Not too hot. I'm a wreck.
It's a real shame.

195
00:15:43,217 --> 00:15:45,752
Sit down.

196
00:15:45,752 --> 00:15:49,189
No, it won't be
possible tonight.

197
00:15:49,189 --> 00:15:52,759
We haven't sat down
to dinner yet, so...

198
00:15:52,759 --> 00:15:55,796
It can behead
a kangaroo from 150 feet!

199
00:15:55,796 --> 00:15:58,565
Okay, but don't count on us.

200
00:15:58,565 --> 00:16:02,558
Yes, he's here.
Very nice.

201
00:16:03,537 --> 00:16:06,740
He looks like
a real winner.

202
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:10,733
No, I'll bring him over
next week. Bye!

203
00:16:17,284 --> 00:16:19,620
So how are you,
Mr. Pignon?

204
00:16:19,620 --> 00:16:23,613
Very well. Thanks.

205
00:16:24,591 --> 00:16:27,794
The message on your machine
is so witty.

206
00:16:27,794 --> 00:16:31,632
Really? I wanted it
to be original.

207
00:16:31,632 --> 00:16:33,467
I'm still laughing.

208
00:16:33,467 --> 00:16:36,270
Everybody comments on it.

209
00:16:36,270 --> 00:16:38,505
Friends ask me
to record their messages.

210
00:16:38,505 --> 00:16:42,498
- I can see why.
- I could do yours...

211
00:16:42,910 --> 00:16:45,212
- No need.
- It'd take a minute.

212
00:16:45,212 --> 00:16:46,713
No, it's fine as it is,

213
00:16:46,713 --> 00:16:49,483
even if it might be
a little conservative for you.

214
00:16:49,483 --> 00:16:52,553
I'm delighted to meet you.

215
00:16:52,553 --> 00:16:54,521
Likewise.

216
00:16:54,521 --> 00:16:56,957
Since you called me
at the Ministry,

217
00:16:56,957 --> 00:16:59,393
I've been walking on air.

218
00:16:59,393 --> 00:17:03,230
I thought it was a joke.
Did I sound dumb on the phone?

219
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:06,833
Yes... I mean, no.
You were perfect.

220
00:17:06,833 --> 00:17:10,237
A big publisher wanting
to do a book on my models,

221
00:17:10,237 --> 00:17:12,639
inviting me to dinner...

222
00:17:12,639 --> 00:17:15,008
you've changed my life.

223
00:17:15,008 --> 00:17:19,001
The book project isn't
quite final yet...

224
00:17:19,713 --> 00:17:23,706
I brought photos
of my finest pieces.

225
00:17:26,486 --> 00:17:29,690
- The Eiffel Tower.
- Superb.

226
00:17:29,690 --> 00:17:32,226
- Took me eight months.
- It shows.

227
00:17:32,226 --> 00:17:35,329
- You do them at night?
- And on weekends.

228
00:17:35,329 --> 00:17:37,397
- Whenever I have time.
- Are you married?

229
00:17:37,397 --> 00:17:39,766
Yes... I mean, no.

230
00:17:39,766 --> 00:17:41,735
- The Tancarville Bridge.
- Great!

231
00:17:41,735 --> 00:17:45,038
- So are you married or not?
- Well...

232
00:17:45,038 --> 00:17:47,774
- my wife left me.
- She did?

233
00:17:47,774 --> 00:17:49,676
For a friend of mine.

234
00:17:49,676 --> 00:17:51,645
Those things happen.

235
00:17:51,645 --> 00:17:54,715
A guy I knew at the Ministry.
Not a bad guy.

236
00:17:54,715 --> 00:17:57,284
I invited him home.
She fell for him.

237
00:17:57,284 --> 00:18:01,277
I don't know why,
because he's no genius.

238
00:18:03,490 --> 00:18:05,659
You know how many matches
in this one?

239
00:18:05,659 --> 00:18:08,996
- What do you mean, no genius?
- The guy she ran off with.

240
00:18:08,996 --> 00:18:11,865
What a dumbbell!

241
00:18:11,865 --> 00:18:13,600
Come on, say a number.

242
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:16,336
Dumber than... I mean,
you're pretty smart,

243
00:18:16,336 --> 00:18:18,472
so how would he rate
against you?

244
00:18:18,472 --> 00:18:22,465
Sorry to be so blunt,
but he's quite the idiot!

245
00:18:22,676 --> 00:18:24,411
My God!

246
00:18:24,411 --> 00:18:25,912
So?

247
00:18:25,912 --> 00:18:29,049
How could she run off
with an idiot?

248
00:18:29,049 --> 00:18:33,042
I agree. He only talks
about windsurfing!

249
00:18:33,587 --> 00:18:37,357
- Can I meet him?
- You like windsurfing?

250
00:18:37,357 --> 00:18:39,092
I love it.

251
00:18:39,092 --> 00:18:43,085
Then you'll love Benjamin!
We call him Dumbo.

252
00:18:44,398 --> 00:18:48,391
He's in the phone book.
Under Benjamin, not Dumbo.

253
00:18:54,007 --> 00:18:55,976
So, how many matches?

254
00:18:55,976 --> 00:18:57,744
2,000?

255
00:18:57,744 --> 00:19:01,737
346,422!

256
00:19:03,450 --> 00:19:06,386
That's not all.
How many tubes of glue?

257
00:19:06,386 --> 00:19:09,856
We're going
to that dinner!

258
00:19:09,856 --> 00:19:13,026
- You can walk?
- I'll try.

259
00:19:13,026 --> 00:19:15,362
- You got a car?
- Sure.

260
00:19:15,362 --> 00:19:19,355
If you drive, we'll manage.
Help me up.

261
00:19:21,468 --> 00:19:25,461
Here we go.

262
00:19:27,374 --> 00:19:29,843
You okay?

263
00:19:29,843 --> 00:19:33,836
Take it easy.

264
00:19:34,381 --> 00:19:36,950
- 37!
- What?

265
00:19:36,950 --> 00:19:40,943
37 tubes of glue.

266
00:19:41,588 --> 00:19:45,581
We'll have a wonderful evening,
Mr. Pignon!

267
00:19:49,429 --> 00:19:53,422
I'm so sorry.
Are you hurt?

268
00:19:53,834 --> 00:19:57,827
There might be broken bones.

269
00:20:01,541 --> 00:20:03,744
- Now what?
- A chiropractor!

270
00:20:03,744 --> 00:20:06,680
- No need.
- A buddy of mine. He's great.

271
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:09,816
- I don't need him!
- He's the best in Courbevoie.

272
00:20:09,816 --> 00:20:13,809
I don't want him!
Go home, I'll be fine.

273
00:20:14,020 --> 00:20:16,189
- What about dinner?
- It's off.

274
00:20:16,189 --> 00:20:20,182
I'm in no shape now!

275
00:20:22,696 --> 00:20:24,064
The machine's on.

276
00:20:24,064 --> 00:20:27,401
We're out.
Speak after the beep.

277
00:20:27,401 --> 00:20:30,737
Your message
is a bit flat.

278
00:20:30,737 --> 00:20:34,074
It's me. I won't be
coming home tonight.

279
00:20:34,074 --> 00:20:37,911
I may never
come home again.

280
00:20:37,911 --> 00:20:40,814
Sorry to tell you this
on a machine,

281
00:20:40,814 --> 00:20:42,983
but maybe it's best.

282
00:20:42,983 --> 00:20:46,976
Goodbye, Pierre.

283
00:20:51,725 --> 00:20:55,718
I'll be going now.

284
00:20:55,929 --> 00:20:58,231
- Sure you don't need anything?
- Yes.

285
00:20:58,231 --> 00:21:02,224
Everything's fine.
Good night.

286
00:21:07,040 --> 00:21:08,842
Sorry...

287
00:21:08,842 --> 00:21:12,835
I forgot my briefcase.

288
00:21:17,451 --> 00:21:21,087
I'm with you, Mr. Brochant.
All the way!

289
00:21:21,087 --> 00:21:25,080
- Thanks a lot. Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

290
00:21:25,659 --> 00:21:29,463
- What can I do for you?
- Nothing. I'm fine. Good night.

291
00:21:29,463 --> 00:21:32,666
I really know
what you're going through.

292
00:21:32,666 --> 00:21:34,901
I'd like to be left alone!

293
00:21:34,901 --> 00:21:36,937
I said that when she left me,

294
00:21:36,937 --> 00:21:39,906
and I nearly died of grief
alone in my house.

295
00:21:39,906 --> 00:21:41,808
Plus, you've got a bad back.

296
00:21:41,808 --> 00:21:44,611
She hasn't left me.
She's a bit depressed.

297
00:21:44,611 --> 00:21:47,080
She'll be back.
Now go home, and good night!

298
00:21:47,080 --> 00:21:51,073
"She'll be back."
That's what I said for two years.

299
00:21:52,652 --> 00:21:54,688
I'm off to bed.
Turn out the lights.

300
00:21:54,688 --> 00:21:56,957
Can't I call
my chiropractor buddy?

301
00:21:56,957 --> 00:21:59,726
- No!
- He's great.

302
00:21:59,726 --> 00:22:02,696
And cheap. Know what
he charges for house calls?

303
00:22:02,696 --> 00:22:06,689
I'm with Pr. Sorbier
of the West Side Hospital.

304
00:22:07,100 --> 00:22:08,969
I don't need your buddy!

305
00:22:08,969 --> 00:22:12,105
Yours may be good,
but look at you now!

306
00:22:12,105 --> 00:22:14,274
Because you fell on me!

307
00:22:14,274 --> 00:22:18,267
Why do I even argue
with this jerk?

308
00:22:18,645 --> 00:22:21,948
You're like a horse
that missed a jump.

309
00:22:21,948 --> 00:22:24,150
At the track, they'd put you
out of your misery.

310
00:22:24,150 --> 00:22:26,520
Go away, Mr. Pignon!

311
00:22:26,520 --> 00:22:28,688
This could be dangerous.

312
00:22:28,688 --> 00:22:32,292
If the spinal marrow is affected,
you might get paralyzed.

313
00:22:32,292 --> 00:22:35,996
Then, you'll need
quite the miracle!

314
00:22:35,996 --> 00:22:39,989
- Call Sorbier!
- That's better!

315
00:22:41,668 --> 00:22:45,661
- What's his number?
- Look in that book.

316
00:23:00,854 --> 00:23:03,990
Pr. Sorbier, please.
For Pierre Brochant.

317
00:23:03,990 --> 00:23:07,594
- Pierre Brochant?
- I need the doctor right away.

318
00:23:07,594 --> 00:23:11,587
- There's no doctor here.
- Sorry, I dialed a wrong number.

319
00:23:11,798 --> 00:23:14,167
I skipped a line.

320
00:23:14,167 --> 00:23:18,160
- The handwriting's so tiny.
- Who cares?! Just hang up!

321
00:23:18,805 --> 00:23:20,874
Yes, I'm at his place.

322
00:23:20,874 --> 00:23:22,976
Yes, he's here.

323
00:23:22,976 --> 00:23:25,345
No, he's in
pretty bad shape.

324
00:23:25,345 --> 00:23:28,682
He's got a bad back.

325
00:23:28,682 --> 00:23:31,084
He can't move,
he's spread out on the floor

326
00:23:31,084 --> 00:23:35,088
- like a sack of potatoes.
- Who are you talking to?

327
00:23:35,088 --> 00:23:37,991
Who am I talking to?

328
00:23:37,991 --> 00:23:40,026
Really?

329
00:23:40,026 --> 00:23:43,330
Then I can tell you
he's in very bad shape.

330
00:23:43,330 --> 00:23:45,699
His wife left him, too.

331
00:23:45,699 --> 00:23:49,002
- He's broken, body and soul!
- Stop that!

332
00:23:49,002 --> 00:23:52,995
I must go.
He's about to lose it. Bye!

333
00:23:54,107 --> 00:23:58,100
- It was your sister!
- I don't have a sister.

334
00:23:58,411 --> 00:24:00,280
You don't?

335
00:24:00,280 --> 00:24:03,883
I said, "Who is this?"
She said, "His sister."

336
00:24:03,883 --> 00:24:05,819
He called Marlene!

337
00:24:05,819 --> 00:24:07,754
She's not your sister?

338
00:24:07,754 --> 00:24:10,056
Her name is
Marlene Hissister!

339
00:24:10,056 --> 00:24:14,049
How could I know?
She said, "Marlene, his sister."

340
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:18,153
- It's confusing.
- Give me that phone.

341
00:24:18,765 --> 00:24:22,135
Hurry! If my wife's gone,
she'll come running.

342
00:24:22,135 --> 00:24:24,904
All I need
is a nymphomaniac!

343
00:24:24,904 --> 00:24:28,897
She's a nympho, too?
Oh, my!

344
00:24:32,245 --> 00:24:34,948
Stop it, will you?

345
00:24:34,948 --> 00:24:37,183
If I call,
she'll go on for hours!

346
00:24:37,183 --> 00:24:41,176
Tell her my wife's back.
Hurry, damn it!

347
00:24:41,454 --> 00:24:44,057
- My wife's back, everything's well.
- Really?

348
00:24:44,057 --> 00:24:47,727
- That's what you say!
- Right, sorry.

349
00:24:47,727 --> 00:24:51,720
Marlene Hissister!

350
00:25:00,874 --> 00:25:03,043
Marlene Hissister?

351
00:25:03,043 --> 00:25:07,036
It's me again. I'm calling to say
Mrs. Brochant came home.

352
00:25:07,313 --> 00:25:09,049
Yes, a moment ago.

353
00:25:09,049 --> 00:25:13,042
She's fine, Mr. Brochant is fine,
everybody's fine.

354
00:25:13,787 --> 00:25:16,990
His back is sore,
but he's taking it better.

355
00:25:16,990 --> 00:25:18,958
Say goodbye!

356
00:25:18,958 --> 00:25:22,951
I'm not really a friend of his.
He likes my models.

357
00:25:24,097 --> 00:25:28,090
I make matchstick models
of engineering feats...

358
00:25:29,169 --> 00:25:32,505
the Tancarville Bridge,
the Golden Gate Bridge...

359
00:25:32,505 --> 00:25:35,775
- She doesn't care!
- She's very interested!

360
00:25:35,775 --> 00:25:39,713
- Don't tie up my phone line!
- Sorry, I have to go now.

361
00:25:39,713 --> 00:25:42,782
He needs me and in his shape,
I can't leave him alone.

362
00:25:42,782 --> 00:25:44,017
Oh my God!

363
00:25:44,017 --> 00:25:46,920
Alone? His wife isn't back?

364
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:48,488
What?

365
00:25:48,488 --> 00:25:52,459
Sure she's back...
but she stepped out.

366
00:25:52,459 --> 00:25:55,128
She hasn't walked out,
she stepped out...

367
00:25:55,128 --> 00:25:57,163
to throw out the garbage.

368
00:25:57,163 --> 00:25:59,265
What is this?

369
00:25:59,265 --> 00:26:03,136
Aries, with Gemini ascending.

370
00:26:03,136 --> 00:26:06,940
- Aries don't lie. I'm not lying.
- Enough!

371
00:26:06,940 --> 00:26:10,933
I'll be right over.

372
00:26:11,111 --> 00:26:14,848
She said, "I'll be right over,"
and hung up.

373
00:26:14,848 --> 00:26:18,318
Give me that phone!

374
00:26:18,318 --> 00:26:21,154
Sorry, I played it too cool.

375
00:26:21,154 --> 00:26:25,147
I didn't expect her
to be so cunning.

376
00:26:30,897 --> 00:26:32,832
It's you, darling.

377
00:26:32,832 --> 00:26:35,502
I'll drop off the dogs
and be right over.

378
00:26:35,502 --> 00:26:37,904
Don't!

379
00:26:37,904 --> 00:26:40,807
My wife'll be home any minute.
Don't come over!

380
00:26:40,807 --> 00:26:43,843
Sorry, but I doubt
she'll be returning.

381
00:26:43,843 --> 00:26:46,980
Know what I think?
She's back with Leblanc.

382
00:26:46,980 --> 00:26:50,973
Leblanc? Why even bring him up?
It's over between them!

383
00:26:51,818 --> 00:26:55,811
I say she's with no one!
Please stay home tonight, okay?

384
00:26:57,991 --> 00:27:01,461
That nut won't listen!

385
00:27:01,461 --> 00:27:05,165
You can go now.
I need to be alone.

386
00:27:05,165 --> 00:27:08,835
Can I help you to your room?
You can't sleep on the floor!

387
00:27:08,835 --> 00:27:12,828
Get me to the sofa.

388
00:27:13,506 --> 00:27:15,508
Slowly.

389
00:27:15,508 --> 00:27:19,501
Look ahead.

390
00:27:20,547 --> 00:27:22,982
- They're all alike, eh?
- What?

391
00:27:22,982 --> 00:27:26,975
I gather yours ran off
with someone too.

392
00:27:27,287 --> 00:27:29,823
She ran off with nobody.

393
00:27:29,823 --> 00:27:31,958
Mine ran off
with nobody, also,

394
00:27:31,958 --> 00:27:35,428
because Benjamin
is a nobody.

395
00:27:35,428 --> 00:27:39,299
- But she still ran off with him!
- Hadn't we said goodbye?

396
00:27:39,299 --> 00:27:41,100
Yes, I'll be off.

397
00:27:41,100 --> 00:27:45,093
I'll get you some water
for the pills, then I'll leave.

398
00:27:47,207 --> 00:27:49,275
Is he a friend of yours?

399
00:27:49,275 --> 00:27:53,268
Go to hell!

400
00:27:59,619 --> 00:28:03,612
Briefcase!

401
00:28:08,561 --> 00:28:12,554
When you asked about my life,
I didn't say "Go to hell."

402
00:28:13,199 --> 00:28:16,402
Farewell, Mr. Brochant.

403
00:28:16,402 --> 00:28:20,395
Leblanc was my best friend.
We quarreled two years ago. Okay?

404
00:28:21,074 --> 00:28:23,409
Over what?

405
00:28:23,409 --> 00:28:26,012
He made a pass at your wife?

406
00:28:26,012 --> 00:28:28,181
No, I stole her from him.

407
00:28:28,181 --> 00:28:31,384
He lived with Christine.
She left him for me.

408
00:28:31,384 --> 00:28:34,554
They wrote a novel together
and brought it to me.

409
00:28:34,554 --> 00:28:37,156
Then what?

410
00:28:37,156 --> 00:28:40,627
I took both the novel
and Christine.

411
00:28:40,627 --> 00:28:44,620
All you windsurfers
steal your friends' wives?

412
00:28:45,565 --> 00:28:48,401
I'm no windsurfer!
Give me a break!

413
00:28:48,401 --> 00:28:50,270
But you told me...

414
00:28:50,270 --> 00:28:52,472
I don't do it enough
to swipe my friends'...

415
00:28:52,472 --> 00:28:54,407
what am I saying?

416
00:28:54,407 --> 00:28:57,644
Is your curiosity satisfied?

417
00:28:57,644 --> 00:29:00,580
Why don't you call him?

418
00:29:00,580 --> 00:29:04,083
- Who?
- Him. To see if she's with him!

419
00:29:04,083 --> 00:29:07,320
I call and say,
"Did the woman I stole come back?"

420
00:29:07,320 --> 00:29:09,555
At least, you'd know.

421
00:29:09,555 --> 00:29:13,548
I called Benjamin and asked,
"Have you left with Florence?"

422
00:29:13,660 --> 00:29:17,653
He said yes and hung up.
At least I knew.

423
00:29:19,332 --> 00:29:21,734
- What if I called him?
- You?

424
00:29:21,734 --> 00:29:25,038
I can say, "I'm a friend
of Mrs. Brochant's,

425
00:29:25,038 --> 00:29:28,241
- where can I reach her?"
- And he won't suspect a thing!

426
00:29:28,241 --> 00:29:30,743
- I'm just trying to help.
- Thanks,

427
00:29:30,743 --> 00:29:34,113
but she's not with him.
I need rest.

428
00:29:34,113 --> 00:29:36,149
I won't insist.

429
00:29:36,149 --> 00:29:40,142
Good night!

430
00:29:42,055 --> 00:29:46,048
- Mr. Pignon?
- Yes?

431
00:29:46,092 --> 00:29:49,996
If I tell you exactly what to say,
could you do it?

432
00:29:49,996 --> 00:29:53,989
Sometimes I feel like
you think I'm an idiot.

433
00:29:54,434 --> 00:29:57,603
Of course I can!
What do I say?

434
00:29:57,603 --> 00:30:00,106
We could use
the book they wrote.

435
00:30:00,106 --> 00:30:02,976
Tell him you're
a movie producer.

436
00:30:02,976 --> 00:30:05,378
You've read the book and
want the movie rights.

437
00:30:05,378 --> 00:30:06,713
Good idea!

438
00:30:06,713 --> 00:30:10,149
Then casually, you ask
about his co-author.

439
00:30:10,149 --> 00:30:13,119
- What co-author?
- My wife!

440
00:30:13,119 --> 00:30:16,756
- He wrote it with her!
- Right. I'm sorry.

441
00:30:16,756 --> 00:30:19,292
- It'll never work!
- It will!

442
00:30:19,292 --> 00:30:22,295
- It's not easy, but I got it.
- Not easy?

443
00:30:22,295 --> 00:30:25,465
You're a producer, okay?
You have a company in Paris.

444
00:30:25,465 --> 00:30:27,734
No, he knows everybody here.
Foreign.

445
00:30:27,734 --> 00:30:30,203
American? German?

446
00:30:30,203 --> 00:30:32,672
Belgian! That's it!

447
00:30:32,672 --> 00:30:35,475
- Why Belgian?
- It suits you.

448
00:30:35,475 --> 00:30:39,468
You're a Belgian producer, you read
"The Merry-Go-Round,"

449
00:30:39,645 --> 00:30:42,148
and want to buy
the movie rights, okay?

450
00:30:42,148 --> 00:30:46,141
- Is it a good book?
- It's awful. Why?

451
00:30:46,519 --> 00:30:48,821
- It bothers me.
- Why?

452
00:30:48,821 --> 00:30:52,814
If it's awful,
why do I want the rights?

453
00:30:54,327 --> 00:30:56,796
Mr. Pignon?
You're not a producer, are you?

454
00:30:56,796 --> 00:30:58,064
No.

455
00:30:58,064 --> 00:30:59,766
- You're not Belgian, either?
- No.

456
00:30:59,766 --> 00:31:03,759
So you're not calling about the
book, you're calling about my wife!

457
00:31:06,272 --> 00:31:09,475
That's tricky,
but clever as hell!

458
00:31:09,475 --> 00:31:12,812
- What's his number?
- 01.47.45...

459
00:31:12,812 --> 00:31:15,715
never mind, I'll dial it.

460
00:31:15,715 --> 00:31:19,519
- His name is Juste Leblanc.
- He has no first name?

461
00:31:19,519 --> 00:31:23,512
I told you, Juste Leblanc.

462
00:31:25,324 --> 00:31:29,317
Leblanc's his name,
Juste his first name.

463
00:31:31,064 --> 00:31:35,057
Mr. Pignon, your first
name's Franois.

464
00:31:35,334 --> 00:31:39,327
Just think his is Juste.

465
00:31:39,472 --> 00:31:41,774
We're wasting time.

466
00:31:41,774 --> 00:31:44,544
My wife wrote under
her maiden name, Le Guirrec.

467
00:31:44,544 --> 00:31:47,146
She's from Brittany?

468
00:31:47,146 --> 00:31:50,349
- Please, stay focused!
- Sorry.

469
00:31:50,349 --> 00:31:53,486
At the end, ask him

470
00:31:53,486 --> 00:31:55,588
where you can contact
Christine Le Guirrec.

471
00:31:55,588 --> 00:31:57,523
I'll put on
the loudspeaker.

472
00:31:57,523 --> 00:32:01,516
- Go to it.
- With a Belgian accent?

473
00:32:06,399 --> 00:32:10,369
Can I talk
to Mr. Juste Leblanc?

474
00:32:10,369 --> 00:32:11,871
Speaking.

475
00:32:11,871 --> 00:32:14,407
Good evening, Mr. Leblanc,

476
00:32:14,407 --> 00:32:17,877
George Van Brueghel here,
sorry to bother you so late.

477
00:32:17,877 --> 00:32:21,447
I'm a Belgian producer,
I just got in from Belgium,

478
00:32:21,447 --> 00:32:25,440
and I'm very interested
in your novel...

479
00:32:26,352 --> 00:32:28,888
"The Merry-Go-Round"!

480
00:32:28,888 --> 00:32:32,725
I'd like to discuss buying
the movie rights.

481
00:32:32,725 --> 00:32:34,694
Is this a joke?

482
00:32:34,694 --> 00:32:37,230
Not at all, why?

483
00:32:37,230 --> 00:32:39,599
- Etienne?
- What?

484
00:32:39,599 --> 00:32:43,592
Cut it out, I know it's you.

485
00:32:44,337 --> 00:32:48,330
You're mistaken. I'm not Etienne,
I'm a producer from Brussels.

486
00:32:49,542 --> 00:32:52,712
- What company?
- Sorry?

487
00:32:52,712 --> 00:32:55,214
What's your company called?

488
00:32:55,214 --> 00:32:57,650
Flatland Films.

489
00:32:57,650 --> 00:33:00,720
A young, but dynamic company.

490
00:33:00,720 --> 00:33:04,724
- And you're interested in my novel?
- Very interested.

491
00:33:04,724 --> 00:33:07,393
- For a movie or TV?
- A movie.

492
00:33:07,393 --> 00:33:10,696
