they haven't done it yet.

980
01:03:31,048 --> 01:03:35,041
- Why is he not answering?
- He's too busy!

981
01:03:39,724 --> 01:03:41,993
- Pascal Meneaux?
- Yes.

982
01:03:41,993 --> 01:03:45,986
He sounds tired.
That's bad.

983
01:03:46,030 --> 01:03:47,732
That's a bad sign.

984
01:03:47,732 --> 01:03:50,368
Sorry to bother you.

985
01:03:50,368 --> 01:03:53,771
I'm calling on behalf
of Mr. Roussin.

986
01:03:53,771 --> 01:03:54,772
Yes?

987
01:03:54,772 --> 01:03:58,109
He's on a plane,
but he has a message for you.

988
01:03:58,109 --> 01:03:59,543
Go ahead.

989
01:03:59,543 --> 01:04:02,079
- Brochant knows everything.
- What?

990
01:04:02,079 --> 01:04:04,382
He's coming
to wreck your place!

991
01:04:04,382 --> 01:04:05,583
Nice going.

992
01:04:05,583 --> 01:04:07,451
Who is this?

993
01:04:07,451 --> 01:04:09,720
A friend of Roussin's.

994
01:04:09,720 --> 01:04:11,655
Brochant's coming over,
and not alone.

995
01:04:11,655 --> 01:04:15,259
He's with three
of his toughest pals.

996
01:04:15,259 --> 01:04:17,428
He's crazy!
His wife's not here!

997
01:04:17,428 --> 01:04:20,097
You're not with her?

998
01:04:20,097 --> 01:04:22,266
She canceled out.

999
01:04:22,266 --> 01:04:26,259
Roussin said,
"He's with Mrs. Brochant."

1000
01:04:26,637 --> 01:04:30,630
Not at all. I'm with the wife
of guy who's auditing me!

1001
01:04:34,612 --> 01:04:36,414
What?

1002
01:04:36,414 --> 01:04:38,582
The jerk's hounded me
for months.

1003
01:04:38,582 --> 01:04:42,575
I'm screwing his wife,
not Mrs. Brochant!

1004
01:04:47,258 --> 01:04:49,727
May I use your phone?

1005
01:04:49,727 --> 01:04:53,720
Certainly.

1006
01:04:55,433 --> 01:04:58,769
She went shopping
this afternoon.

1007
01:04:58,769 --> 01:05:02,762
I asked her to take a form
to Meneaux's office.

1008
01:05:03,607 --> 01:05:07,600
And bingo!

1009
01:05:08,279 --> 01:05:10,614
Good evening, Mr. Meneaux.

1010
01:05:10,614 --> 01:05:14,151
Could I speak
to Mrs. Cheval, please?

1011
01:05:14,151 --> 01:05:16,454
You know who I am.

1012
01:05:16,454 --> 01:05:19,223
We're meeting tomorrow
at 9:00, as usual.

1013
01:05:19,223 --> 01:05:21,292
We'll review
your whole case.

1014
01:05:21,292 --> 01:05:25,285
Now let me speak
to my wife.

1015
01:05:25,563 --> 01:05:28,099
Charlotte?
Don't try to explain.

1016
01:05:28,099 --> 01:05:31,635
Leave that place at once!

1017
01:05:31,635 --> 01:05:35,628
Of course you can put
your clothes back on!

1018
01:05:37,875 --> 01:05:40,578
I'm not alone.

1019
01:05:40,578 --> 01:05:43,380
I can't talk now.
We'll talk at home.

1020
01:05:43,380 --> 01:05:45,216
Charlotte!

1021
01:05:45,216 --> 01:05:49,209
I did tape the ice-skating
show for you.

1022
01:05:58,329 --> 01:05:59,797
That wine...

1023
01:05:59,797 --> 01:06:01,732
It is a bit coarse.

1024
01:06:01,732 --> 01:06:05,669
- I'm going to puke! The bathroom!
- Here, Lucien!

1025
01:06:05,669 --> 01:06:09,662
First door on the left!

1026
01:06:18,749 --> 01:06:22,742
I said "on the left."

1027
01:06:24,288 --> 01:06:26,490
Interesting room!

1028
01:06:26,490 --> 01:06:30,483
A storage room,
where I keep my old things.

1029
01:06:31,529 --> 01:06:34,532
- It's awful, but I don't care!
- What is?

1030
01:06:34,532 --> 01:06:36,834
He's a tax dodger,
and I don't care!

1031
01:06:36,834 --> 01:06:40,827
Get a hold of yourself.
Run home and take a shower.

1032
01:06:41,906 --> 01:06:45,899
- Want the tape of the soccer game?
- I'm in no mood for that.

1033
01:06:48,245 --> 01:06:50,514
- Goodbye, Mr. Leblanc.
- Goodbye, Mr. Cheval.

1034
01:06:50,514 --> 01:06:53,350
- Goodbye, Mr. Brochant.
- Thanks for all your help.

1035
01:06:53,350 --> 01:06:55,819
Don't mention it.
We'll meet again soon.

1036
01:06:55,819 --> 01:06:59,812
I'm going to audit you.
All this is suspect.

1037
01:07:03,694 --> 01:07:07,687
He recovered pretty fast!

1038
01:07:22,713 --> 01:07:25,549
- Where can she be?
- I'll go home.

1039
01:07:25,549 --> 01:07:28,686
- If she calls, I'll call.
- Thanks.

1040
01:07:28,686 --> 01:07:32,690
- Goodbye, Mr. Pignon.
- Goodbye.

1041
01:07:32,690 --> 01:07:34,525
Is everyone leaving?

1042
01:07:34,525 --> 01:07:38,518
Yes, you can leave too.

1043
01:07:41,398 --> 01:07:42,733
Yes?

1044
01:07:42,733 --> 01:07:44,468
Speaking.

1045
01:07:44,468 --> 01:07:48,461
I'm her husband.
Is something wrong?

1046
01:07:50,674 --> 01:07:53,611
Which hospital?
I'm coming!

1047
01:07:53,611 --> 01:07:56,046
She had a car accident.
She's at the hospital.

1048
01:07:56,046 --> 01:07:58,716
- Is it serious?
- Just a concussion,

1049
01:07:58,716 --> 01:08:02,386
- but they're keeping her overnight.
- I could drive you.

1050
01:08:02,386 --> 01:08:06,379
No, thanks.

1051
01:08:24,708 --> 01:08:27,911
Pierre, it's me.

1052
01:08:27,911 --> 01:08:30,080
I know you're there.

1053
01:08:30,080 --> 01:08:32,916
You're not being nice.

1054
01:08:32,916 --> 01:08:36,909
You promised to leave your wife.
Look how you treat me now!

1055
01:08:38,322 --> 01:08:42,315
Answer me!
I need you. I'm not well!

1056
01:08:44,461 --> 01:08:46,597
Pick up the phone!

1057
01:08:46,597 --> 01:08:49,466
If you don't,
I'll do something silly!

1058
01:08:49,466 --> 01:08:53,103
His wife had an accident.
He's at the hospital.

1059
01:08:53,103 --> 01:08:56,106
- An accident?
- It's not serious, but...

1060
01:08:56,106 --> 01:08:59,677
- Serves him right!
- Don't say that, Marlene.

1061
01:08:59,677 --> 01:09:01,779
Serves him right!
He's mean!

1062
01:09:01,779 --> 01:09:05,449
His wife's in the hospital,
and I'll kill myself.

1063
01:09:05,449 --> 01:09:09,442
Don't kill yourself.
Try to understand, it's been hell...

1064
01:09:10,954 --> 01:09:13,657
He's a bastard!

1065
01:09:13,657 --> 01:09:17,650
Fuck, my glass...
look at that mess.

1066
01:09:18,128 --> 01:09:22,099
Why did I fall
for that bastard?

1067
01:09:22,099 --> 01:09:24,568
Sorry, I have to hang up.

1068
01:09:24,568 --> 01:09:27,638
Don't hang up!

1069
01:09:27,638 --> 01:09:30,607
Talk to me.
It makes me feel better.

1070
01:09:30,607 --> 01:09:32,109
Hang up!

1071
01:09:32,109 --> 01:09:35,112
- She's suicidal.
- It's blackmail.

1072
01:09:35,112 --> 01:09:36,780
Where are my keys?

1073
01:09:36,780 --> 01:09:40,773
Don't do anything silly!
Swear you won't!

1074
01:09:41,852 --> 01:09:45,845
You're nice.
But he's a bastard!

1075
01:09:47,124 --> 01:09:49,960
One hell of a bastard!

1076
01:09:49,960 --> 01:09:51,995
Don't say that.

1077
01:09:51,995 --> 01:09:55,988
He's so mean!
Even in his way of having fun!

1078
01:09:56,066 --> 01:09:57,568
I have to go.

1079
01:09:57,568 --> 01:10:01,561
If he hadn't hurt his back,
he'd be making fun of some guy.

1080
01:10:02,973 --> 01:10:05,008
What do you mean?

1081
01:10:05,008 --> 01:10:06,844
Hang up!

1082
01:10:06,844 --> 01:10:09,847
Didn't he tell you?

1083
01:10:09,847 --> 01:10:13,784
Every week, they hold
a dinner game.

1084
01:10:13,784 --> 01:10:17,777
They invite idiots and
make fun of them all night!

1085
01:10:28,065 --> 01:10:32,058
Let's go!

1086
01:10:32,836 --> 01:10:34,972
Your briefcase.

1087
01:10:34,972 --> 01:10:37,207
Quick.
I'm in a hurry.

1088
01:10:37,207 --> 01:10:41,200
- Mr. Brochant.
- Yes?

1089
01:10:41,779 --> 01:10:44,715
What was tonight's
dinner for?

1090
01:10:44,715 --> 01:10:46,683
For friends
who admired your work!

1091
01:10:46,683 --> 01:10:49,686
- Let's go!
- Were there other guests?

1092
01:10:49,686 --> 01:10:52,489
Let's talk in the elevator.

1093
01:10:52,489 --> 01:10:55,726
What kind of guests?

1094
01:10:55,726 --> 01:10:58,462
Why these questions?

1095
01:10:58,462 --> 01:11:02,032
How do you pick your guests?

1096
01:11:02,032 --> 01:11:05,769
Get to the point.

1097
01:11:05,769 --> 01:11:09,762
Was I invited
to your dinner for idiots?

1098
01:11:20,951 --> 01:11:23,253
It's you, darling.
I was just leaving.

1099
01:11:23,253 --> 01:11:26,690
How are you?

1100
01:11:26,690 --> 01:11:28,859
What do you mean?

1101
01:11:28,859 --> 01:11:32,852
I love you, and
I won't leave you alone!

1102
01:11:33,931 --> 01:11:36,500
I've learned a lot tonight.

1103
01:11:36,500 --> 01:11:40,504
I need you!

1104
01:11:40,504 --> 01:11:42,973
To hell with her!

1105
01:11:42,973 --> 01:11:46,966
She's not my girlfriend!
That retard made it up!

1106
01:11:48,045 --> 01:11:52,038
I'm coming.
We'll talk it over, okay?

1107
01:12:00,224 --> 01:12:03,927
The retard is leaving.
But first, answer this:

1108
01:12:03,927 --> 01:12:07,920
Did you invite me
to a dinner for idiots?

1109
01:12:12,569 --> 01:12:14,671
Look, in one evening,

1110
01:12:14,671 --> 01:12:18,664
you've avenged all the idiots
who ever attended our dinners.

1111
01:12:19,943 --> 01:12:22,679
Good night, Mr. Pignon.

1112
01:12:22,679 --> 01:12:26,550
- She's right. You're mean.
- So I'm mean!

1113
01:12:26,550 --> 01:12:30,543
My wife says it, and
everyone agrees... I'm mean.

1114
01:12:31,788 --> 01:12:34,057
You can put it
on my answering machine,

1115
01:12:34,057 --> 01:12:38,050
"Brochant is a meanie!"

1116
01:12:38,629 --> 01:12:41,331
Don't mix sedatives
and alcohol.

1117
01:12:41,331 --> 01:12:43,901
Why not?
It's the moral of the story...

1118
01:12:43,901 --> 01:12:47,905
Brochant the meanie gets drunk
alone in his big place,

1119
01:12:47,905 --> 01:12:51,898
while nice Pignon goes home saying,
"The bastard got punished!"

1120
01:12:52,576 --> 01:12:56,569
"Brochant's a meanie,
Pignon's a beanie!"

1121
01:13:02,185 --> 01:13:04,221
Now what?

1122
01:13:04,221 --> 01:13:06,256
I need the number
to the West Side Hospital.

1123
01:13:06,256 --> 01:13:10,249
He's at it again!

1124
01:13:10,561 --> 01:13:13,096
Thanks.

1125
01:13:13,096 --> 01:13:17,089
You won't get her.
It's a public hospital.

1126
01:13:18,869 --> 01:13:20,237
West Side Hospital.

1127
01:13:20,237 --> 01:13:24,230
Mrs. Christine Brochant, please.
She was in a car accident.

1128
01:13:24,341 --> 01:13:28,334
No calls for patients after 6:00 PM.
Call tomorrow.

1129
01:13:29,246 --> 01:13:33,239
- There you go!
- I must speak to Mrs. Brochant.

1130
01:13:34,251 --> 01:13:36,987
This is Pr. Sorbier.

1131
01:13:36,987 --> 01:13:39,122
Sorry, sir.
Please hold on.

1132
01:13:39,122 --> 01:13:43,115
I'm in a rush, dear.
Hurry!

1133
01:13:44,795 --> 01:13:48,788
- Mrs. Brochant for you, Professor.
- Thanks, dear.

1134
01:13:50,233 --> 01:13:54,226
Stop this farce.
She just hung up on me.

1135
01:13:56,607 --> 01:14:00,043
Pr. Sorbier for you.

1136
01:14:00,043 --> 01:14:03,714
Thanks.

1137
01:14:03,714 --> 01:14:05,782
Mrs. Brochant?

1138
01:14:05,782 --> 01:14:07,284
Yes, doctor.

1139
01:14:07,284 --> 01:14:11,277
I'm not Pr. Sorbier.

1140
01:14:12,289 --> 01:14:16,282
- Who is this?
- I'm your husband's idiot.

1141
01:14:19,162 --> 01:14:21,064
What?

1142
01:14:21,064 --> 01:14:24,034
We briefly met.
My name's Pignon,

1143
01:14:24,034 --> 01:14:28,027
I'm your husband's idiot
for that dinner.

1144
01:14:29,439 --> 01:14:31,274
I'm listening.

1145
01:14:31,274 --> 01:14:34,845
I just found out
why I was invited,

1146
01:14:34,845 --> 01:14:37,147
and I'm in a state of shock.

1147
01:14:37,147 --> 01:14:41,151
You were in a crash,
and so was I!

1148
01:14:41,151 --> 01:14:43,854
Hello?

1149
01:14:43,854 --> 01:14:45,422
Yes, I'm here.

1150
01:14:45,422 --> 01:14:48,458
I'm not calling because
I feel sorry for myself.

1151
01:14:48,458 --> 01:14:51,194
I feel sorry for him.

1152
01:14:51,194 --> 01:14:53,864
He may not be
the meanest of men,

1153
01:14:53,864 --> 01:14:56,667
but he's the unhappiest.

1154
01:14:56,667 --> 01:15:00,203
I heard you tell him
not to visit you.

1155
01:15:00,203 --> 01:15:03,206
He was so lost,
so miserable,

1156
01:15:03,206 --> 01:15:07,199
that I forgot I was the idiot
and decided to call.

1157
01:15:07,310 --> 01:15:10,047
- Mrs. Brochant?
- Yes?

1158
01:15:10,047 --> 01:15:14,040
My wife left me two years ago.
That day, my life was shattered.

1159
01:15:16,086 --> 01:15:19,356
I survived
by making my models,

1160
01:15:19,356 --> 01:15:22,859
but deep down,
I'm still a wreck.

1161
01:15:22,859 --> 01:15:26,852
I wish that on no one,
not even your husband.

1162
01:15:28,799 --> 01:15:32,169
Is he there?

1163
01:15:32,169 --> 01:15:34,037
What?

1164
01:15:34,037 --> 01:15:38,030
He's feeding you the lines
of this moving drama?

1165
01:15:38,508 --> 01:15:42,501
I swear it was my idea
to call you.

1166
01:15:42,846 --> 01:15:44,715
He fed me nothing.

1167
01:15:44,715 --> 01:15:48,285
Is he beside you?

1168
01:15:48,285 --> 01:15:52,278
No, I'm in a phone booth.

1169
01:15:54,858 --> 01:15:58,851
He doesn't love me.
He loves no one.

1170
01:15:59,396 --> 01:16:01,231
Mrs. Brochant,
for two hours,

1171
01:16:01,231 --> 01:16:04,534
I saw your husband
try to find you.

1172
01:16:04,534 --> 01:16:07,070
He even called Pascal Meneaux,

1173
01:16:07,070 --> 01:16:11,063
who was in the arms
of a woman who wasn't you!

1174
01:16:12,075 --> 01:16:14,511
He called Meneaux?

1175
01:16:14,511 --> 01:16:15,879
He did.

1176
01:16:15,879 --> 01:16:18,915
You can't imagine
what he did out of love for you.

1177
01:16:18,915 --> 01:16:22,908
He made up with his best friend,
dumped his girlfriend.

1178
01:16:23,253 --> 01:16:26,923
He even braved
a tax inspector!

1179
01:16:26,923 --> 01:16:30,916
He tidied up his whole life,
in an exemplary way.

1180
01:16:31,795 --> 01:16:35,788
Now he's alone in his big apartment,
mixing alcohol and pills.

1181
01:16:37,567 --> 01:16:40,170
I'm worried about him.

1182
01:16:40,170 --> 01:16:44,163
I know one can die of love,
Mrs. Brochant.

1183
01:16:46,443 --> 01:16:50,436
I'll think it over.
Thanks for calling.

1184
01:16:51,982 --> 01:16:54,050
Don't mention it.

1185
01:16:54,050 --> 01:16:58,043
Goodbye.

1186
01:17:00,390 --> 01:17:04,383
She'll call back.

1187
01:17:08,231 --> 01:17:10,200
- Mr. Pignon?
- Yes?

1188
01:17:10,200 --> 01:17:14,193
We're going to the next dinner.
But this time, you're taking me!

1189
01:17:14,237 --> 01:17:17,174
- And I'll win first prize.
- I'm exhausted.

1190
01:17:17,174 --> 01:17:19,910
Being smart is very tiring.

1191
01:17:19,910 --> 01:17:23,346
- I'll try it sometime.
- Promise me one thing.

1192
01:17:23,346 --> 01:17:24,581
Just ask.

1193
01:17:24,581 --> 01:17:27,450
Think twice before
you call anyone an idiot.

1194
01:17:27,450 --> 01:17:31,443
I promise. I swear.

1195
01:17:32,255 --> 01:17:34,391
Here he is,
Mrs. Brochant!

1196
01:17:34,391 --> 01:17:38,094
I thought you were
in a phone booth.

1197
01:17:38,094 --> 01:17:40,096
You idiot!

1198
01:17:40,096 --> 01:17:42,833
- No, I'm back at his place.
- What an idiot!

1199
01:17:42,833 --> 01:17:44,601
I can explain!

1200
01:17:44,601 --> 01:17:47,270
- What an idiot!
- I'll call her back!

1201
01:17:47,270 --> 01:17:51,263
- I'll call her back, it'll be fine!
- What an idiot!